\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Three-qubit W state $(|001\rangle + |010\rangle + |100\rangle )/\sqrt  {3}$ in Dimensional Circular Notation. This state represents a different SLOCC entanglement class than GHZ. If any one qubit is measured, the remaining two qubits remain entangled. The DCN cube shows non-zero amplitudes on three corners sharing no common face.}}{7}{figure.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:dcn-3qubit-w}{{6}{7}{Three-qubit W state $(|001\rangle + |010\rangle + |100\rangle )/\sqrt {3}$ in Dimensional Circular Notation. This state represents a different SLOCC entanglement class than GHZ. If any one qubit is measured, the remaining two qubits remain entangled. The DCN cube shows non-zero amplitudes on three corners sharing no common face}{figure.6}{}}
