\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Separable three-qubit state $|0++\rangle = (|000\rangle + |010\rangle )/\sqrt  {2}$ in Dimensional Circular Notation. This state is product across qubit 2 (the MSB $Q_2$), as evidenced by the non-zero amplitudes lying in a 2D sub-plane ($Q_2 = 0$). The green connecting lines indicate separability along the corresponding dimension.}}{8}{figure.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:dcn-3qubit-separable}{{7}{8}{Separable three-qubit state $|0++\rangle = (|000\rangle + |010\rangle )/\sqrt {2}$ in Dimensional Circular Notation. This state is product across qubit 2 (the MSB $Q_2$), as evidenced by the non-zero amplitudes lying in a 2D sub-plane ($Q_2 = 0$). The green connecting lines indicate separability along the corresponding dimension}{figure.7}{}}
