\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {33}{\ignorespaces Negativity visualization: the partial transpose $\rho ^{T_A}$ of an entangled state has negative eigenvalues (shown in red). The negativity $N(\rho )$ measures the total "volume" of these negative regions, providing a quantifier of bipartite entanglement. Negativity $N(\rho ) = \frac  {||\rho ^{T_A}||_1 - 1}{2}$: The "volume" of negative eigenvalues in the partial transpose indicates entanglement. For separable states, all eigenvalues are positive; for entangled states, negative eigenvalues appear.}}{27}{figure.33}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:negativity-visualization}{{33}{27}{Negativity visualization: the partial transpose $\rho ^{T_A}$ of an entangled state has negative eigenvalues (shown in red). The negativity $N(\rho )$ measures the total "volume" of these negative regions, providing a quantifier of bipartite entanglement. Negativity $N(\rho ) = \frac {||\rho ^{T_A}||_1 - 1}{2}$: The "volume" of negative eigenvalues in the partial transpose indicates entanglement. For separable states, all eigenvalues are positive; for entangled states, negative eigenvalues appear}{figure.33}{}}
\newlabel{fig:negativity-visualization@cref}{{[figure][33][]33}{[1][26][]27}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {34}{\ignorespaces Coffman-Kundu-Wootters (CKW) inequality visualization for three qubits. The triangle inequality shows that the squared entanglement $C_{A(BC)}^2$ (hypotenuse) must be at least as large as the sum of squared pairwise entanglements $C_{AB}^2 + C_{AC}^2$. The tangle $\tau $ represents the genuine tripartite entanglement not captured by pairwise measures. CKW inequality visualization: For three qubits, the squared concurrences satisfy $C_{AB}^2 + C_{AC}^2 \leq C_{A(BC)}^2$. The tangle $\tau = C_{A(BC)}^2 - C_{AB}^2 - C_{AC}^2$ represents the "excess" genuine tripartite entanglement beyond pairwise correlations.}}{27}{figure.34}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ckw-inequality}{{34}{27}{Coffman-Kundu-Wootters (CKW) inequality visualization for three qubits. The triangle inequality shows that the squared entanglement $C_{A(BC)}^2$ (hypotenuse) must be at least as large as the sum of squared pairwise entanglements $C_{AB}^2 + C_{AC}^2$. The tangle $\tau $ represents the genuine tripartite entanglement not captured by pairwise measures. CKW inequality visualization: For three qubits, the squared concurrences satisfy $C_{AB}^2 + C_{AC}^2 \leq C_{A(BC)}^2$. The tangle $\tau = C_{A(BC)}^2 - C_{AB}^2 - C_{AC}^2$ represents the "excess" genuine tripartite entanglement beyond pairwise correlations}{figure.34}{}}
\newlabel{fig:ckw-inequality@cref}{{[figure][34][]34}{[1][26][]27}}
